1.00	Accidia	Sloth (deadly sin)	In the Christian moral tradition, sloth is one of the seven capital sins, often called the seven deadly sins; these sins are called deadly sins because they destroy the charity in a person's heart and thus may lead to eternal death.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c9/Abraham_Bloemaert_-_Parable_of_the_Wheat_and_the_Tares_-_Walters_372505.jpg/220px-Abraham_Bloemaert_-_Parable_of_the_Wheat_and_the_Tares_-_Walters_372505.jpg
